WEBVTT

00:01.238 --> 00:03.575
- My son was imprisoned too.
- Says your son died

00:03.577 --> 00:05.310
of a heart attack.
- There's something

00:05.312 --> 00:07.245
they're not telling me.
- That kid?

00:07.247 --> 00:08.580
He didn't just up and get
in a fight without good reason.

00:08.582 --> 00:10.515
You don't know
what you talking about.

00:10.517 --> 00:11.683
- Look, are the guards corrupt?
- No! He just died!

00:11.685 --> 00:13.351
I need Mike to drop that case.

00:13.353 --> 00:14.853
You telling me
to go back on my word

00:14.855 --> 00:16.454
because your client's
bullying you?

00:16.456 --> 00:18.323
It's one pro Bono.
He can drop it.

00:18.325 --> 00:20.325
If I give you an assignment,
you do it.

00:20.327 --> 00:23.128
Since I got here, I have had
to take shit from Louis.

00:23.130 --> 00:24.629
And now you're asking me
to waste my time

00:24.631 --> 00:27.132
and my ability
on something like this.

00:27.134 --> 00:28.900
We can't have you
setting a precedent

00:28.902 --> 00:31.503
that Alex's clients
can run roughshod all over us.

00:31.505 --> 00:33.605
The only reason
that you're pissed about this

00:33.607 --> 00:37.675
is your new honeysuckle friend
canceled lunch on you for me.

00:37.677 --> 00:39.477
I can't let them get away
with this

00:39.479 --> 00:41.246
without handing it off
to the one lawyer I know

00:41.248 --> 00:42.714
who cares enough
to see this thing through.

00:42.716 --> 00:45.450
If our firm is associated
with that case,

00:45.452 --> 00:47.452
we lose a huge client.
- I'm not working on it.

00:47.454 --> 00:48.887
Then you're gonna put that
in writing and you're gonna

00:48.889 --> 00:50.488
deliver it to Alex's client.

00:50.490 --> 00:52.223
I was just wondering.
Have you redone

00:52.225 --> 00:53.525
the assignment
that Rachel gave you?

00:53.527 --> 00:55.226
Not yet.

00:55.228 --> 00:57.195
I had a ton on my plate.
- You're fired.

00:57.197 --> 00:58.496
What kind of best man
would I be

00:58.498 --> 01:00.198
if I didn't offer for you
to have it here?

01:00.200 --> 01:01.499
Pretty shitty one,
if you ask me.

01:01.501 --> 01:04.402
- Congratulations.
- Thanks, Harvey.

01:07.307 --> 01:10.909
[keys jingle]

01:10.911 --> 01:13.178
You sure he's not in?

01:13.180 --> 01:14.746
I hate to walk in
on the man

01:14.748 --> 01:16.681
in his tighty-whities.
- [laughs]

01:16.683 --> 01:18.449
I don't think Harvey
wears tighty-whities.

01:18.451 --> 01:20.251
Oh, Jesus Christ, Rachel.

01:20.253 --> 01:23.321
I don't wanna think about
what the man wears.

01:24.257 --> 01:25.957
Well...

01:25.959 --> 01:27.725
what do you think?

01:27.727 --> 01:29.460
This is great!

01:29.462 --> 01:31.663
If you're a...
Bachelor pushing 50

01:31.665 --> 01:34.199
and you need to impress
women.

01:35.635 --> 01:37.368
No, no, no, no.
What are you doing?

01:37.370 --> 01:38.937
Don't go in his fridge!
Rachel.

01:38.939 --> 01:40.738
The man gave us his keys.
Trust me.

01:40.740 --> 01:42.674
He knows we're gonna
go through his shit.

01:42.676 --> 01:44.976
So basically you came here
to look at what he eats

01:44.978 --> 01:47.245
and to say that this is
a "no" for the wedding.

01:47.247 --> 01:49.414
Of course it's a no.
But the fact is...

01:49.416 --> 01:51.449
why are we even talking
venue at all

01:51.451 --> 01:52.984
when you don't even
have a date?

01:52.986 --> 01:54.953
We're gonna get around
to that.

01:54.955 --> 01:57.555
Mm-hmm.
Just like you...

01:57.557 --> 02:00.291
got around
to the announcement?

02:00.293 --> 02:02.327
- What?
- Your mother said

02:02.329 --> 02:04.295
that she arranged
for a photographer,

02:04.297 --> 02:06.764
but you cancelled.
Same with the florist.

02:06.766 --> 02:09.300
What's going on?
- Nothing is going on.

02:09.301 --> 02:11.636
Mike and I are both
really busy

02:11.638 --> 02:13.805
getting our careers
off the ground right now.

02:13.807 --> 02:15.473
Rachel, that's just it.

02:15.475 --> 02:17.475
If you can't focus
on your wedding,

02:17.477 --> 02:19.444
how are you gonna
make time to focus

02:19.446 --> 02:22.013
on your marriage?

02:22.015 --> 02:25.283
Now, that's why
you came here, isn't it?

02:25.285 --> 02:27.452
To give me
sweet advice like that.

02:27.454 --> 02:30.521
Well, that, and to tell
the mighty Harvey Specter

02:30.523 --> 02:33.725
I took his toilet bowl
for a test drive.

02:33.727 --> 02:37.362
Dad... you're not
doing that.

02:37.364 --> 02:38.796
You know how to

02:38.798 --> 02:41.366
suck the fun out of
everything, don'tcha?

02:41.368 --> 02:43.334
[softly]
Oh, my God.

02:43.336 --> 02:46.337
<i>[contemplative music]</i>

02:46.339 --> 02:51.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:51.444 --> 02:53.745
You. Where the hell
is Stephanie?

02:53.747 --> 02:55.413
- She's not here.
- What do you mean,

02:55.415 --> 02:57.348
she's not here?
I just got off the phone

02:57.350 --> 02:59.350
with a client, and she never
filed their motion to dismiss.

02:59.352 --> 03:01.286
- That's because I fired her.
- You what?!

03:01.288 --> 03:02.854
She was the smartest
fourth-year we had!

03:02.856 --> 03:04.789
She was also insubordinate,
and I made a decision.

03:04.791 --> 03:06.491
I don't give a shit
what you made.

03:06.493 --> 03:08.426
She was working for me
on Delta Securities,

03:08.428 --> 03:10.561
and I need her back.
- Okay, Louis,

03:10.563 --> 03:12.030
I'm not getting her back.

03:12.032 --> 03:13.665
What kind of message
does that send

03:13.667 --> 03:15.500
to the other associates?
- Better than the one

03:15.502 --> 03:17.402
we're sending out now
which is that this firm

03:17.404 --> 03:19.037
is a Goddamn joke.
- Louis, you need to calm down

03:19.039 --> 03:20.571
right now before this
goes in the wrong direction,

03:20.573 --> 03:22.340
'cause this isn't about
Stephanie.

03:22.342 --> 03:23.875
This is about Tara
and the fact that you

03:23.877 --> 03:25.510
haven't been dealing with her.
- This has nothing to do

03:25.512 --> 03:26.711
with Tara.
This is about Harvey

03:26.713 --> 03:28.513
running this firm
into the ground.

03:28.515 --> 03:30.048
And how exactly
has he been doing that?

03:30.050 --> 03:31.683
Let me run it down for you.
I'm pissed at him.

03:31.685 --> 03:33.451
Mike's pissed at him.
And the last time I saw you,

03:33.453 --> 03:35.420
you were pissed at him.
So instead of telling me

03:35.422 --> 03:36.854
that you're not gonna hire
Stephanie back,

03:36.856 --> 03:39.457
why don't you go tell
the lord God almighty

03:39.459 --> 03:41.059
that if he is not careful,

03:41.061 --> 03:44.095
he's not gonna have
a kingdom to rule over anymore!

03:44.097 --> 03:47.098
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:47.100 --> 03:50.868
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:50.870 --> 03:53.905
- Morning.
- Harvey, I'm sort of busy,

03:53.907 --> 03:56.074
so if you're here
to shoot the shit...

03:56.076 --> 03:58.076
I'm here
to give you this.

03:58.078 --> 04:00.778
- What's this?
- It's my way of saying thanks.

04:00.780 --> 04:03.681
- For what?
- You know what.

04:03.683 --> 04:06.517
Harvey, I dropped the suit
because you asked me to.

04:06.519 --> 04:08.353
You don't have to give me
anything in return.

04:08.355 --> 04:10.788
Has anyone ever taught you
how to be gracious?

04:10.790 --> 04:12.824
Open the file.

04:16.663 --> 04:18.396
This's a pro Bono.

04:18.398 --> 04:19.863
I figured you didn't
get to complete

04:19.866 --> 04:22.400
your one-for-you this time,
so it's only fair.

04:22.402 --> 04:23.901
Plus, you didn't want me
to sue you

04:23.903 --> 04:25.870
for violating our agreement.
- Doesn't look good

04:25.872 --> 04:28.673
to have Robin coming after
Batman for breach of contract.

04:28.675 --> 04:30.875
Seriously, Mike, I know
how hard that was for you,

04:30.877 --> 04:33.511
and I don't want there
to be any bad blood

04:33.513 --> 04:34.779
between you and Alex.
- I don't have a problem

04:34.781 --> 04:36.481
with Alex, Harvey.
- You sure?

04:36.483 --> 04:38.750
I'm sure.

04:41.654 --> 04:43.388
- Sure?
- Good. Yeah.

04:43.390 --> 04:44.722
- All good?
- You should go.

04:44.724 --> 04:47.759
<i>[light music]</i>

04:47.761 --> 04:51.629
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:51.631 --> 04:53.164
Let me guess.

04:53.166 --> 04:55.466
You're bored being C.O.O.,
you miss me,

04:55.468 --> 04:56.768
and you want back
on my desk.

04:56.770 --> 04:58.136
I never want back
on your desk, Harvey,

04:58.138 --> 04:59.737
and I'm here to tell you

04:59.739 --> 05:01.873
that your honeymoon
as Managing Partner is over.

05:01.875 --> 05:03.608
Is this about me
not calling a vote

05:03.610 --> 05:04.942
after you undermined me
in that meeting?

05:04.944 --> 05:06.711
I'm gonna let that go

05:06.713 --> 05:08.579
because you need to understand
that right now

05:08.581 --> 05:09.914
people are mad at you.
- Relax, Donna.

05:09.916 --> 05:11.849
I took care of Mike.
- Good for you.

05:11.851 --> 05:13.818
You're one for three.
- Maybe you didn't know this,

05:13.820 --> 05:16.621
but that's good enough to get
you into the Hall of Fame.

05:16.623 --> 05:18.656
You know what, Harvey,
instead of being so arrogant,

05:18.658 --> 05:20.825
maybe you could figure out
a way to keep all of us happy.

05:20.827 --> 05:22.794
Starting with your number two.
- What's that supposed to mean?

05:22.796 --> 05:24.862
It means Louis is out
of his mind at the moment.

05:24.864 --> 05:27.732
You poured fuel on the fire,
and if you asked me

05:27.734 --> 05:30.435
to choose between the two of you
for Managing Partner right now,

05:30.437 --> 05:31.702
I'd choose Alex Williams.

05:31.704 --> 05:32.970
- Donna--
- Listen to me, Harvey.

05:32.972 --> 05:34.772
If making me C.O.O.

05:34.774 --> 05:36.441
wasn't just some
bullshit move

05:36.443 --> 05:37.842
to make me feel good,

05:37.844 --> 05:39.577
you'll get your head
out of your ass,

05:39.579 --> 05:40.912
listen to what
I'm telling you,

05:40.914 --> 05:44.515
and realize
you've got a problem.

05:44.517 --> 05:47.518
<i>[somber music]</i>

05:47.520 --> 05:50.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:51.791 --> 05:55.760
<i>♪ See the money,</i>
<i>wanna stay for your meal ♪</i>

05:55.762 --> 05:59.197
<i>♪ Get another piece of pie</i>
<i>for your wife ♪</i>

05:59.199 --> 06:02.567
<i>♪ Everybody wanna know</i>
<i>how it feel ♪</i>

06:02.569 --> 06:05.803
<i>♪ Everybody wanna see</i>
<i>what it's like ♪</i>

06:05.805 --> 06:09.207
<i>♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,</i>
<i>I don't mind ♪</i>

06:09.209 --> 06:12.677
<i>♪ Me and Missy is so busy,</i>
<i>busy making money ♪</i>

06:12.679 --> 06:14.545
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

06:14.547 --> 06:15.684
<i>♪ All step back,</i>
<i>I'm 'bout to dance ♪</i>

06:15.685 --> 06:19.685
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ Suits 7x04 ♪</font></b>
<font color="#00FFFF">Divide and Conquer</font>
Original Air Date on August 2, 2017

06:19.686 --> 06:21.588
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

06:21.589 --> 06:23.589
