<font color="#00FFFF">@elder_man</font>

06:23.590 --> 06:26.391
<i> [soft piano in background]</i>

06:26.393 --> 06:29.160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:29.162 --> 06:30.562
Harvey.

06:30.564 --> 06:32.397
Jessica.

06:32.399 --> 06:34.532
Retirement suits you.

06:34.534 --> 06:37.135
- I'm not retired.
- You look retired.

06:37.137 --> 06:39.537
I look relaxed.
There's a difference.

06:39.539 --> 06:41.406
Now, what's going on,
Harvey?

06:41.408 --> 06:43.475
The last time you flew
to Chicago this often,

06:43.477 --> 06:45.110
Michael was still playing.

06:45.112 --> 06:48.013
I'm in a situation
at the office.

06:48.015 --> 06:51.316
Well, the first thing
to do when you're in trouble

06:51.318 --> 06:53.585
is admit to yourself what you
did to get yourself there.

06:53.587 --> 06:55.320
What do you think I did?

06:55.322 --> 06:57.422
I made a deal with Mike
to come back.

06:57.424 --> 06:59.424
I made Donna a partner
without thinking it through.

06:59.426 --> 07:01.626
I hired someone
against Louis's wishes.

07:01.628 --> 07:04.129
And all those things
are colliding with each other

07:04.131 --> 07:06.131
into a big pile of
"people hate Harvey."

07:06.133 --> 07:08.066
Well, at least it's not
a big pile of

07:08.068 --> 07:10.068
"people hate Jessica."
- That's your advice?

07:10.070 --> 07:11.569
[chuckles] No.
No.

07:11.571 --> 07:15.373
Harvey, my advice is to give
a big piece of new business

07:15.375 --> 07:18.176
to the person least likely
to let anything go.

07:18.178 --> 07:20.278
- Louis.
- Nine times outta ten.

07:20.280 --> 07:23.148
I can't just manufacture
that overnight.

07:23.150 --> 07:24.649
Harvey, do you remember
that time

07:24.651 --> 07:28.319
we poached Trotter Systems
from Zane?

07:29.523 --> 07:32.657
You gotta be shitting me.
That was a prearranged deal?

07:32.659 --> 07:34.459
I worked my ass off
to get Trotter.

07:34.461 --> 07:37.062
You did.
And you completely forgot

07:37.064 --> 07:39.130
that you were pissed at me
about some bullshit

07:39.132 --> 07:40.698
neither one of us
can remember anymore.

07:42.335 --> 07:44.702
- Rook to bishop four.
- Exactly.

07:44.704 --> 07:48.206
Now, take a look at your menu,
'cause I'm starving.

07:48.208 --> 07:50.108
When, exactly,
do you think

07:50.110 --> 07:52.177
I'm gonna stop coming
to you with these things?

07:52.179 --> 07:53.411
The truth is, Harvey,

07:53.413 --> 07:56.281
you don't need to come
to me anymore.

07:56.283 --> 07:58.283
You just do it
'cause you miss me.

07:58.285 --> 08:01.286
<i>[mellow music]</i>

08:01.288 --> 08:04.155
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:05.092 --> 08:06.491
Hey. Can I talk to you
for a second?

08:06.493 --> 08:08.326
Yeah. But I only have
a few minutes.

08:08.328 --> 08:10.195
I have court.

08:10.197 --> 08:12.530
I met with my dad at Harvey's
apartment this morning.

08:12.532 --> 08:15.200
Don't tell me.
He said a bachelor pad

08:15.202 --> 08:18.303
is no place for his
special little girl

08:18.305 --> 08:20.138
to celebrate the biggest
day of her life.

08:20.140 --> 08:21.506
Well, Mike,
you have to admit

08:21.508 --> 08:23.174
the only reason
that we changed it

08:23.176 --> 08:24.576
from the Plaza
in the first place

08:24.578 --> 08:26.244
was because we didn't want
the attention.

08:26.246 --> 08:28.646
But now that you're
a legitimate lawyer...

08:28.648 --> 08:30.582
we don't have to worry
about that.

08:30.584 --> 08:33.118
Rachel, it's okay.
I just want you to be happy.

08:33.120 --> 08:34.652
- So you're not mad.
- Not at all.

08:34.654 --> 08:37.688
Good. Because now that
it <i> is</i> at the Plaza,

08:37.691 --> 08:40.158
I called and made an appointment
with the wedding team

08:40.159 --> 08:42.193
for us to go over
some menu options.

08:42.195 --> 08:44.195
Wait, wait, wait.
You made an appointment

08:44.197 --> 08:46.764
in between when I said it
was okay a second ago and now?

08:46.766 --> 08:48.533
Yeah, y-you didn't
just notice me do that?

08:48.535 --> 08:51.269
It was <i> crazy</i> fast!
- You're fast.

08:51.271 --> 08:55.273
Mike, seriously, I appreciate
you being so understanding.

08:55.275 --> 08:57.542
The appointment
is tonight at 7:00.

08:57.544 --> 08:59.777
Rachel, I have a meeting
tonight with my pro Bono,

08:59.779 --> 09:02.413
and I can't put it off.
Can you do this one without me?

09:02.415 --> 09:04.549
Of course I can, but
I wanted us to do it together.

09:04.551 --> 09:05.683
Rachel, listen to me.

09:05.685 --> 09:07.452
I know you...right?

09:07.454 --> 09:09.220
You're gonna have
a thousand questions.

09:09.222 --> 09:11.189
You're gonna want to
narrow down the choices.

09:11.191 --> 09:13.725
I promise you I will be
at every other meeting.

09:13.727 --> 09:15.793
Okay.
I'll take care of it.

09:15.795 --> 09:18.163
- All right. Love you.
- Love you, too.

09:18.165 --> 09:21.166
<i>[soft music]</i>

09:21.168 --> 09:24.302
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:24.304 --> 09:26.571
Why aren't you playing
from the men's tees?

09:26.573 --> 09:28.573
If you're here to insist

09:28.575 --> 09:30.408
that my daughter gets married
in that love shack of yours,

09:30.410 --> 09:32.177
that ship has sailed.
- Oh, I don't care

09:32.179 --> 09:33.611
if she gets married
at the Taj Mahal.

09:33.613 --> 09:35.647
I'm here to take you up
on Jessica's arrangement.

09:35.649 --> 09:37.215
Yeah. What arrangement
was that?

09:37.217 --> 09:38.583
The one
where you do me a favor

09:38.585 --> 09:39.717
and I give you
a big one in return.

09:39.719 --> 09:41.452
What the hell do you think

09:41.454 --> 09:42.720
letting Katrina Bennett
and Company

09:42.722 --> 09:44.455
walk over to you
without a fight was?

09:44.457 --> 09:46.257
I didn't ask you
to do that.

09:46.259 --> 09:48.459
I don't care whether
you asked me or not.

09:48.461 --> 09:50.662
It's been a thin quarter,
and I'm no Goddamn Santa Claus.

09:50.664 --> 09:52.463
- Robert.
- Okay, Harvey.

09:52.465 --> 09:53.731
You want a favor?
I'll give you one.

09:53.733 --> 09:56.234
Instead of you asking me
for a handout,

09:56.236 --> 09:57.702
you should watch your
backside,

09:57.704 --> 10:00.471
because you've got a missile
coming straight for you.

10:00.473 --> 10:02.507
- Bratton Gould.
- Yes. Bratton Gould.

10:02.509 --> 10:04.342
What'd you think
they were gonna do

10:04.344 --> 10:05.843
when you took their senior
partner and marquee client

10:05.845 --> 10:08.413
out from under their noses?
- I knew they'd try

10:08.415 --> 10:10.548
to retaliate, but I didn't think
it would happen this fast.

10:10.550 --> 10:12.383
Well, today's the day.

10:12.385 --> 10:14.419
Let me tell you something.

10:14.421 --> 10:16.487
I have no love for them.

10:16.489 --> 10:18.523
So I'll do whatever
I can to help.

10:18.525 --> 10:21.693
But like I said,
it's been a thin quarter.

10:21.695 --> 10:24.629
And I'm not letting you
get one of my clients.

10:24.631 --> 10:28.366
<i>[somber music]</i>

10:28.368 --> 10:30.301
[background chatter]

10:30.303 --> 10:31.736
Oliver.
What are you doing here?

10:31.738 --> 10:33.504
- I need to talk to you.
- If it's about the case,

10:33.506 --> 10:34.872
I can't do that,
and you know it.

10:34.874 --> 10:36.708
- Please, I just need a minute.
- Oliver,

10:36.710 --> 10:38.276
we signed an agreement.
I can't be doing this.

10:38.278 --> 10:39.477
Not to mention
I have other cases.

10:39.479 --> 10:40.845
The guard's testimony

10:40.847 --> 10:42.680
doesn't match
their version of events,

10:42.682 --> 10:44.616
and I can't prove it.
What do you mean?

10:44.618 --> 10:46.818
The prison claims
the doctor was on the premises.

10:46.820 --> 10:48.486
The guard says
they had to call him.

10:48.488 --> 10:49.854
I asked for
surveillance video

10:49.856 --> 10:51.456
to see if he was
already there.

10:51.458 --> 10:52.690
They said they can't
disclose it

10:52.692 --> 10:54.392
because it would violate
HIPAA rules.

10:54.394 --> 10:55.660
[whispers] Shit.
What about surveillance

10:55.662 --> 10:57.495
of the parking lot?
- They're saying

10:57.497 --> 10:58.863
that footage is gone.
- Then they're definitely

10:58.865 --> 11:00.465
hiding something.
- But I can't prove it.

11:00.467 --> 11:01.799
And if I don't get
something,

11:01.801 --> 11:03.501
I can't move forward
with this case.

11:03.503 --> 11:07.672
<i>[anticipatory music]</i>

11:07.674 --> 11:09.574
Listen, Oliver,
like I said,

11:09.576 --> 11:10.808
I can't discuss this case.

11:10.810 --> 11:12.744
What but what I can
tell you is that

11:12.746 --> 11:14.479
if you can convince someone
that you already have something,

11:14.481 --> 11:16.681
that's the best way
to get them in the room.

11:16.683 --> 11:19.751
I get it--I convince them
I have the doctor's time card,

11:19.753 --> 11:21.452
and he was nowhere near
that place,

11:21.454 --> 11:23.488
I can get them to settle.
- Like I said,

11:23.490 --> 11:26.424
I can't help you.

11:26.426 --> 11:28.526
Good not talking
to you, Mike.

11:28.528 --> 11:32.597
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:32.599 --> 11:34.599
Harvey, we need to talk,
and it can't wait.

11:34.601 --> 11:36.668
Then walk with me, because
Bratton's getting ready

11:36.670 --> 11:38.436
to poach our clients,
and Louis needs to know.

11:38.438 --> 11:39.771
He already knows.

11:39.773 --> 11:41.572
They're making a play
for Delta Securities,

11:41.574 --> 11:42.874
and that's not their only move.
- Don't tell me.

11:42.876 --> 11:44.375
They're coming after
my clients too.

11:44.377 --> 11:45.710
AC Technologies.

11:45.712 --> 11:47.445
But, Harvey,
they're not trying to poach.

11:47.447 --> 11:48.780
They're suing
for patent infringement.

11:48.782 --> 11:50.682
Aw, shit!

11:50.684 --> 11:53.651
Louis, whatever you're doing
to keep Delta Securities,

11:53.653 --> 11:55.553
take a breath.
I need you to listen

11:55.555 --> 11:57.555
to what I have to say.
- Oh, I'm done listening to you.

11:57.557 --> 11:59.524
You wanna manage this firm
into the ground,

11:59.526 --> 12:01.492
you go right ahead.
But when your bullshit

12:01.494 --> 12:03.528
puts one of my biggest
clients on the block,

12:03.530 --> 12:05.463
that's when I'm done
playing good soldier.

12:05.465 --> 12:07.332
Listen to me.
Bratton's not just coming

12:07.334 --> 12:09.467
after our clients--they're
trying to divide and conquer.

12:09.469 --> 12:11.469
What are you, Caesar now?
This isn't the Roman Empire.

12:11.471 --> 12:13.705
I don't care what it is.
You think it's a coincidence

12:13.707 --> 12:16.474
they're forcing you to close
on one of your clients

12:16.476 --> 12:18.476
while suing one of mine
for patent infringement?

12:18.478 --> 12:20.578
You're saying I can't
keep my own clients?

12:20.580 --> 12:23.448
Louis, all he's saying
is you should switch clients

12:23.450 --> 12:25.350
and play to your strengths.
- Pass!

12:25.352 --> 12:26.951
Look, I get it--
you don't want Harvey's help

12:26.953 --> 12:28.753
because you're mad at him.
But the least you can do

12:28.755 --> 12:30.655
is to go Alex.
He came from Bratton.

12:30.657 --> 12:32.490
He knows their playbook.
- I don't need their playbook.

12:32.492 --> 12:34.359
And he's the reason
they're coming after us

12:34.361 --> 12:36.594
in the first place.
- Okay, Louis, do it your way.

12:36.596 --> 12:37.895
But you better be
good and ready,

12:37.897 --> 12:39.664
because Bratton knew enough

12:39.666 --> 12:41.532
to come after a client
you almost lost a year ago

12:41.534 --> 12:42.900
and to sue mine
for something

12:42.902 --> 12:44.769
I don't know anything about.

12:44.771 --> 12:47.438
Which means they've got
someone inside this place

12:47.440 --> 12:49.607
telling them what to do.

12:49.609 --> 12:52.577
<i>[lightly tense music]</i>

12:52.579 --> 12:56.447
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:59.788 --> 13:03.423
<i> [soft edgy music]</i>

13:03.425 --> 13:05.224
Louis, can I talk to you
for a second?

13:05.226 --> 13:06.826
No, you can't, because
right at this moment--

13:06.828 --> 13:08.161
I know, you're gonna
meet Delta Securities.

13:08.163 --> 13:09.696
And Harvey already
made it clear

13:09.698 --> 13:11.164
you don't want my help
trying to keep them.

13:11.166 --> 13:13.132
But I have something--
- No buts, Alex.

13:13.134 --> 13:14.801
I don't want your help.
I don't want whatever you have,

13:14.803 --> 13:16.302
because I don't trust ya.
- Trust me? What the hell

13:16.304 --> 13:17.704
are you talking about?
- For all I know,

13:17.706 --> 13:19.372
you were the one who
gave Bratton

13:19.374 --> 13:20.873
the inside information
on us in the first place.

13:20.875 --> 13:22.408
You know what, Louis,
if you think that,

13:22.410 --> 13:24.110
then why the hell don't you
fire me right now?

13:24.112 --> 13:26.913
If it were up to me,
Alex, I would.

13:26.915 --> 13:28.748
<i>Your Honor,</i>
<i>I don't care what they say.</i>

13:28.750 --> 13:30.483
We filed our patent
before they did.

13:30.485 --> 13:32.485
Well, beating
someone off the line

13:32.487 --> 13:34.187
doesn't mean that you didn't
jump the gun to do it.

13:34.189 --> 13:36.122
And our losses
are growing by the day.

13:36.124 --> 13:38.758
Mr. Specter, you'll have your
chance to refute him at trial.

13:38.760 --> 13:40.426
All right, listen,
you want me to be honest?

13:40.428 --> 13:42.161
I haven't felt
prioritized lately.

13:42.163 --> 13:43.763
Are you kidding me?

13:43.765 --> 13:45.865
Who was there when you
had to restructure in '07?

13:45.867 --> 13:48.501
Not to mention,
I just saved your ass last year.

13:48.503 --> 13:50.269
And that was then.
And now I feel like

13:50.271 --> 13:51.504
I can't even get you
on the phone anymore.

13:51.506 --> 13:53.306
- Your Honor--
- That's enough.

13:53.308 --> 13:54.874
I find the evidence
Mr. Walsh is presenting

13:54.876 --> 13:56.743
compelling enough
to let this go forward.

13:56.745 --> 13:58.277
There's only one problem
with that, Your Honor.

13:58.279 --> 13:59.879
We just took one of
their partners,

13:59.881 --> 14:01.280
all of his clients.
They're pissed about it,

14:01.282 --> 14:02.915
and now they want
some get-back.

14:02.917 --> 14:04.751
You being willing
to give me your phone number

14:04.753 --> 14:06.252
isn't the point, Louis.
- Well, it should be.

14:06.254 --> 14:08.287
- Who are you?
- This is Alex Williams,

14:08.289 --> 14:11.491
our newest senior partner, and
he was just stopping by. Alex--

14:11.493 --> 14:13.326
I'm not just the newest
senior partner, Tim.

14:13.328 --> 14:15.895
I'm also the partner
that Bratton Gould just lost.

14:15.897 --> 14:17.530
Your Honor,
they entered into

14:17.532 --> 14:19.432
a fee-waiving partnership
agreement yesterday

14:19.434 --> 14:21.200
with a company that's suddenly
claiming infringement

14:21.202 --> 14:22.969
against
one of our clients today.

14:22.971 --> 14:25.772
Your Honor, their client
caused real damages.

14:25.774 --> 14:27.874
If that's true, those damages
will still be there

14:27.876 --> 14:29.776
in eight weeks,
which means the only reason

14:29.778 --> 14:31.878
you'd be upset right now
is if this action is nonsense.

14:31.880 --> 14:34.947
So which is it--
eight weeks or drop the case?

14:34.949 --> 14:38.317
Morelli's expense reports for
the last three years.

14:38.319 --> 14:40.319
The guy spends
more time in Vegas

14:40.321 --> 14:42.455
than David Blaine.
And now you know.

14:42.457 --> 14:43.956
Just like you already know

14:43.958 --> 14:45.792
that Louis kills
for you out there

14:45.794 --> 14:48.795
whether he's taking
your calls or not.

14:50.331 --> 14:52.198
I'll call you tomorrow
about the acquisition, Louis.

14:52.200 --> 14:54.300
Thank you, Tim.

14:54.302 --> 14:58.471
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

14:58.473 --> 15:00.840
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

15:00.842 --> 15:03.810
Nice move, finding out about
that partnership agreement.

15:03.812 --> 15:05.344
Nice move telling
our client

15:05.346 --> 15:07.346
he's not gonna be billed
for last quarter.

15:07.348 --> 15:09.448
Nothing eases the pain
of a bullshit lawsuit

15:09.450 --> 15:11.384
like cash in your pocket.
- Speaking of which,

15:11.386 --> 15:13.486
I've been back at work
for three weeks now.

15:13.488 --> 15:14.954
Thinking it's time
I got a raise.

15:14.956 --> 15:16.589
Easy, tiger.

15:16.591 --> 15:18.391
Mike, seriously,

15:18.393 --> 15:20.960
I thought you were busy
with that pro Bono.

15:20.962 --> 15:23.029
I am. Donna said
you needed my help,

15:23.031 --> 15:24.430
so...I gave it to you.

15:24.432 --> 15:25.598
Thanks, Robin.

15:25.600 --> 15:28.835
Ah, you're welcome, Batman.

15:28.837 --> 15:31.571
<i>[energetic pop music]</i>

15:31.573 --> 15:38.845
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:41.082 --> 15:42.982
Louis, really...

15:42.984 --> 15:45.551
you didn't have to do this.
- What, are you kidding?

15:45.553 --> 15:47.386
You saved me
after I was an asshole.

15:47.388 --> 15:48.588
You didn't have to do that.
- Yes, I did.

15:48.590 --> 15:50.523
Because I don't care
how you acted.

15:50.525 --> 15:52.525
We're all
in the same boat now.

15:52.527 --> 15:55.528
I guess we are.

15:55.530 --> 15:58.865
Boy, you really...have no
love for your old firm, do you?

15:58.867 --> 16:00.633
If I'm being truthful
with you,

16:00.635 --> 16:02.902
I was never gonna get
where I wanted to be

16:02.904 --> 16:04.503
as long as I was there.

16:04.505 --> 16:07.340
- Name partner.
- Name partner.

16:09.978 --> 16:12.879
You know, I thought of
leaving Pearson Hardman

16:12.881 --> 16:14.080
at one point.
- Bullshit.

16:14.082 --> 16:15.882
No, it's the truth.

16:15.884 --> 16:17.416
I even got a headhunter
and everything.

16:17.418 --> 16:19.452
- I thought you loved it there.
- I do.

16:19.454 --> 16:21.287
Doesn't mean
that I didn't feel

16:21.289 --> 16:23.122
unappreciated and overlooked.

16:23.124 --> 16:25.291
I find it hard to believe
anyone could overlook you.

16:25.293 --> 16:27.126
Well, they did,
and I got to thinking...

16:27.128 --> 16:31.130
I can be the best
lawyer in the world, and...

16:31.132 --> 16:33.332
it won't change
how they see me.

16:33.334 --> 16:35.034
Like you must have been
out sick or something

16:35.036 --> 16:36.669
the day the name partner gods
came down

16:36.671 --> 16:38.437
saying who's gonna make it
up the God damn mountain.

16:38.439 --> 16:40.139
That's exactly right,
and it turns out

16:40.141 --> 16:41.674
I wasn't sick that day,
and neither were you.

16:41.676 --> 16:43.576
And if you ever
feel overlooked again,

16:43.578 --> 16:45.344
I would hope that
you can come to me

16:45.346 --> 16:46.545
so I can help fix it.

16:46.547 --> 16:48.047
Means a lot to me, Louis.

16:48.049 --> 16:50.016
Well...

16:50.018 --> 16:51.584
like you said...

16:51.586 --> 16:53.486
We're all in the same
boat now.

16:53.488 --> 16:57.490
<i>[pop tune resumes]</i>

16:57.492 --> 17:04.329
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:04.332 --> 17:06.933
Rachel, do you have
a minute?

17:06.935 --> 17:08.434
I need your help.
- Yeah, of course.

17:08.435 --> 17:10.970
What's going on?
- I think Stephanie Patel

17:10.972 --> 17:13.539
may be helping Bratton
poach our clients.

17:13.540 --> 17:16.075
What? Since when
is Stephanie at Bratton?

17:16.077 --> 17:18.077
Since this morning,
and it's a long story,

17:18.079 --> 17:20.445
but someone gave them
inside information about us,

17:20.448 --> 17:22.448
and given
that she just started...

17:22.450 --> 17:24.083
I need you to go over
there,

17:24.085 --> 17:25.617
and I need you
to get her to stop.

17:25.619 --> 17:27.520
Me? How am I supposed
to do that?

17:27.521 --> 17:29.355
I don't care if it means
offering her her job back.

17:29.357 --> 17:30.957
But whatever it is,
it has to happen tonight.

17:30.959 --> 17:33.025
Wait, Donna, you can't
be serious right now.

17:33.027 --> 17:35.094
- It's the only way that we--
- Donna, Louis eviscerated her,

17:35.096 --> 17:36.963
and you fired her.
There's no way

17:36.965 --> 17:38.698
she's ever coming back here.
You don't know that.

17:38.700 --> 17:40.700
Not to mention the fact that
I have a meeting this evening

17:40.702 --> 17:42.501
with the wedding planner, so--
I don't care

17:42.503 --> 17:43.970
what you have tonight.
We need to do something,

17:43.972 --> 17:47.039
and we need to do it now.

17:47.041 --> 17:49.141
[quietly] Okay.
What's going on?

17:49.143 --> 17:51.177
Harvey took a chance
on me, Rachel.

17:51.179 --> 17:53.012
He went out on a limb,

17:53.014 --> 17:54.981
and now I have been
promoted to a position

17:54.983 --> 17:56.482
that people think
I'm not ready for.

17:56.484 --> 17:57.984
I didn't mean it
when I said that.

17:57.986 --> 17:59.652
I know that.
But if one of the

17:59.654 --> 18:01.620
first things I did ends up
giving Bratton

18:01.622 --> 18:03.589
a roadmap to picking
this firm apart,

18:03.591 --> 18:05.391
I will never forgive
myself.

18:05.393 --> 18:07.126
And Stephanie might not
talk to you,

18:07.128 --> 18:11.030
but I know
she won't talk to me.

18:11.032 --> 18:12.999
Okay.

18:13.001 --> 18:14.533
I'll go see her, Donna.

18:14.535 --> 18:17.536
<i>[lightly edgy music]</i>

18:17.538 --> 18:19.638
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:21.345 --> 18:23.412
<i> [somber music]</i>

18:23.414 --> 18:24.846
[elevator bell dings]

18:24.848 --> 18:26.748
Anything else you
want me to fix for you

18:26.750 --> 18:28.617
before I get back to my case?
- I'll let you know

18:28.619 --> 18:30.319
after I see Louis.
- What do you mean?

18:30.321 --> 18:31.853
I mean if he couldn't
stop Bratton

18:31.855 --> 18:34.256
from poaching his client,
us doing what we just did

18:34.258 --> 18:36.291
only gives us a split decision.
- But you said Louis

18:36.293 --> 18:37.492
made it clear
he doesn't want your help.

18:37.494 --> 18:38.727
He may not want it,

18:38.729 --> 18:40.429
but if that shit's
not taken care of,

18:40.431 --> 18:42.497
he's getting it whether
he likes it or not.

18:42.499 --> 18:45.534
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

18:45.536 --> 18:47.603
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:47.605 --> 18:49.638
Louis, before you jump
down my throat again--

18:49.640 --> 18:52.407
Relax, Harvey, I'm not
upset with you anymore.

18:52.409 --> 18:55.310
In fact, I even came to
an agreement with Alex

18:55.312 --> 18:57.579
after he locked up
Delta Securities.

18:59.250 --> 19:00.849
- Good.
- What about you?

19:00.851 --> 19:03.285
Do you need my help
with your lawsuit?

19:03.287 --> 19:05.654
It's taken care of.
Don't tell him I said this,

19:05.656 --> 19:07.623
but Mike jumped inside
his phone booth

19:07.625 --> 19:09.524
and put on his Superman
outfit.

19:09.526 --> 19:11.493
Oh, that's great.
So I guess...

19:11.495 --> 19:13.895
this means there's only one
thing left for you to do.

19:13.897 --> 19:18.634
Well, I'd say there's only
one thing left for us to do.

19:18.636 --> 19:20.269
You want me to go
with you?

19:20.271 --> 19:22.904
Your name's up on that
wall, isn't it?

19:28.679 --> 19:29.878
[clears throat]

19:31.715 --> 19:34.316
I see you got
your own office.

19:34.318 --> 19:36.518
What are you doing here?

19:36.520 --> 19:39.354
I know that you didn't
feel valued at Pearson Specter,

19:39.356 --> 19:42.391
and I wanted to apologize
for my part in that.

19:42.393 --> 19:44.359
I also just--I wanted you
to know

19:44.361 --> 19:46.495
that it was never my intention
to get you fired.

19:46.497 --> 19:48.764
I hope you're not here
to offer me my job back.

19:48.766 --> 19:52.801
- And what if I said I was?
- I'd say I wouldn't take it.

19:52.803 --> 19:54.636
Okay...
[exhales] in that case,

19:54.638 --> 19:56.672
I am here to find out

19:56.674 --> 19:59.308
if you're giving your new firm
privileged information.

19:59.310 --> 20:00.609
Let me get this straight.

20:00.611 --> 20:02.878
You have...the nerve
to fire me

20:02.880 --> 20:04.780
and then come here
and accuse me

20:04.782 --> 20:06.848
of breaking
attorney-client privilege?

20:06.850 --> 20:09.451
How else is your firm
getting so much information

20:09.453 --> 20:11.820
on our on-going cases?
- You think I'm the only person

20:11.822 --> 20:13.555
with a grudge
against your firm?

20:13.557 --> 20:15.791
Harvey Specter
declared war on this place

20:15.793 --> 20:17.693
long before I got here.

20:17.695 --> 20:19.895
And not only am I not
giving them information,

20:19.897 --> 20:22.731
they don't need my help,
and they didn't ask for my help.

20:22.733 --> 20:24.733
Just to be clear, Stephanie,
you've lied to me before.

20:24.735 --> 20:26.535
And breaking attorney-client
privilege

20:26.537 --> 20:27.869
is a dis-barrable offense,

20:27.871 --> 20:29.471
and if we find out
that's what's been

20:29.473 --> 20:30.472
happening here--
- No, Rachel,

20:30.474 --> 20:31.640
I didn't lie to you.

20:31.642 --> 20:33.542
Like you said,
I used a loophole.

20:33.544 --> 20:35.844
'Cause I'm a good lawyer,
and I'm also an ethical lawyer.

20:35.846 --> 20:37.713
So if this firm is getting
inside information

20:37.715 --> 20:38.914
from Pearson Specter,

20:38.916 --> 20:40.782
they're not getting it
from me.

20:40.784 --> 20:43.785
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:43.787 --> 20:46.621
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:46.623 --> 20:47.956
Hey, Mike, wait up.

20:47.958 --> 20:49.758
Oliver, what are you
doing here?

20:49.760 --> 20:51.526
I was just waiting for you
so we can grab that beer

20:51.528 --> 20:52.961
like we talked about.
- Except we didn't

20:52.963 --> 20:55.697
talk about grabbing--
- Just walk with me.

20:56.934 --> 20:58.500
God damn it, Oliver,

20:58.502 --> 20:59.901
I told you--
- Mike, relax.

20:59.903 --> 21:02.537
It's over.
The bluff worked.

21:02.539 --> 21:04.573
What do you mean,
it worked?

21:04.575 --> 21:07.542
I got a number,
and it's good.

21:11.482 --> 21:12.647
Shit.

21:12.649 --> 21:13.982
What?

21:13.984 --> 21:16.651
This offer's not just good.
It's too good.

21:16.653 --> 21:18.520
What're you talking about?

21:18.522 --> 21:19.888
You think they're not gonna pay?
- I mean this isn't

21:19.890 --> 21:21.723
the number you give
to make someone go away.

21:21.725 --> 21:23.725
It's a number you give when
you need them to go away.

21:23.727 --> 21:25.527
You're saying you think
there's more cases

21:25.529 --> 21:26.895
like this out there.
- I'm saying that when

21:26.897 --> 21:28.563
someone acts like this,
there's more to find.

21:28.565 --> 21:29.798
Which means you need
to convince Mr. Reyes

21:29.800 --> 21:32.501
to turn this down
and keep looking.

21:32.503 --> 21:34.669
Are you serious, Mike?
This is more money

21:34.671 --> 21:36.705
than this family's ever seen.
- And you convince them--

21:36.707 --> 21:38.740
What? That I'm gonna
find all those other cases?

21:38.742 --> 21:40.809
I already bluffed 'em
once, Mike.

21:40.811 --> 21:43.011
And the only reason we were
able to make this case

21:43.013 --> 21:44.780
is because we threatened
to sue them

21:44.782 --> 21:46.748
over a specific guy.
- Then knock on the door

21:46.750 --> 21:48.617
of everyone that has come
out of that place

21:48.619 --> 21:51.019
and find more guys.
- Mike...

21:52.956 --> 21:55.524
If there are other
victims out there,

21:55.526 --> 21:56.958
I feel for them.

21:56.960 --> 22:00.429
But I'm representing Oscar.
He's suffering.

22:00.431 --> 22:02.697
And I don't feel right
telling him not to do this.

22:02.699 --> 22:04.499
So if you want this done,

22:04.501 --> 22:06.768
you're gonna have to
do it yourself.

22:11.575 --> 22:14.676
[line ringing]

22:15.879 --> 22:19.080
Rachel, please tell me
that you got her to back off.

22:19.082 --> 22:20.882
<i>- It wasn't her.</i>
- What do you mean,

22:20.884 --> 22:22.784
it wasn't her?
It had to be her.

22:22.786 --> 22:24.586
Donna, I apologized to her.

22:24.588 --> 22:26.621
I threatened her,
and I cajoled her.

22:26.623 --> 22:28.657
Trust me--it wasn't her.

22:29.760 --> 22:32.494
Rachel...look,
I didn't mean that stuff

22:32.496 --> 22:35.063
that I said before about not
caring about your appointment.

22:35.065 --> 22:36.998
- I know.
<i>- Well, did you make it?</i>

22:37.000 --> 22:38.834
<i>'Cause I'd hate to think</i>
<i>you missed it for nothing.</i>

22:38.836 --> 22:40.869
I'm walking in right now.
Don't worry.

22:40.871 --> 22:43.004
I'm right on time.

22:43.006 --> 22:45.640
Hi. I'm so sorry.

22:45.642 --> 22:46.908
Rachel Zane.

22:46.910 --> 22:48.610
Deborah Kaplan.

22:48.612 --> 22:50.812
Did my assistant
give you the wrong time?

22:50.814 --> 22:52.113
Because I had us down
for 7:00.

22:52.115 --> 22:53.915
And it's almost 8:00.
I know.

22:53.917 --> 22:56.485
I had an emergency at work,
and it couldn't wait.

22:56.487 --> 22:59.654
But my understanding was
it's a two-hour appointment.

22:59.656 --> 23:01.056
So I was just hoping
that we could

23:01.058 --> 23:03.758
go over as much as possible.
- Of course.

23:03.760 --> 23:05.627
The truth is, I usually
take the first hour

23:05.629 --> 23:06.928
to offer you a glass
of champagne

23:06.930 --> 23:08.864
and try to get to
know you anyway.

23:08.866 --> 23:10.532
But the champagne
is still cold,

23:10.534 --> 23:12.934
and we can just
dive right in.

23:15.806 --> 23:17.138
You still double-billing

23:17.140 --> 23:18.940
to pay for that house
in the Hamptons?

23:18.942 --> 23:21.142
No. I'm working late
to pay for it.

23:21.144 --> 23:23.011
And the one in Vail
and the apartment in Paris.

23:23.013 --> 23:24.679
That's a lotta homes.

23:24.681 --> 23:26.681
Sounds like a man
who's compensating.

23:26.683 --> 23:28.650
[chuckles]

23:28.652 --> 23:30.652
So how're you doing, Harvey?
- Oh, he's doing great.

23:30.654 --> 23:33.088
'Cause we just shut down your
pathetic assault on our firm.

23:33.090 --> 23:34.890
- Is that so?
- You're Goddamn right,

23:34.892 --> 23:36.658
that's so.
Then might I ask what exactly

23:36.660 --> 23:37.926
are you doing here?
We're here to tell you

23:37.928 --> 23:39.661
that if you try this shit
again,

23:39.663 --> 23:41.062
the same thing's gonna happen,

23:41.064 --> 23:42.964
only next time,
we won't just play defense.

23:42.966 --> 23:44.699
We'll hit you with
a tortious interference suit

23:44.701 --> 23:46.735
in the neighborhood
of a billion dollars.

23:46.737 --> 23:48.136
[slap]

23:48.138 --> 23:49.871
Well, you better get ready,

23:49.873 --> 23:52.040
'cause next time...
starts right now.

23:52.042 --> 23:53.808
[laughs]
What, are you kidding?

23:53.810 --> 23:55.143
You already threw
everything you had at us once.

23:55.145 --> 23:57.112
Didn't make a dent.
- Not everything.

23:57.114 --> 24:00.048
By tomorrow morning, I'll be
poaching 20 of your clients,

24:00.050 --> 24:01.950
and I'll be suing
another 20 of his.

24:01.952 --> 24:03.852
And that little trick
you played

24:03.854 --> 24:05.987
in the courtroom today?
It isn't going to

24:05.989 --> 24:07.889
work tomorrow.
- Tom, you made your point.

24:07.891 --> 24:09.925
You're pissed off
that we brought Alex over,

24:09.927 --> 24:11.927
but this doesn't have to--
- I don't give two shits

24:11.929 --> 24:13.094
about Alex Williams.

24:13.096 --> 24:15.797
Lawyers grow on Goddamn trees.

24:15.799 --> 24:17.832
I want my clients back,

24:17.834 --> 24:20.001
and I want the 30 million
in billables

24:20.003 --> 24:21.770
that come along with them,

24:21.772 --> 24:23.805
hand-delivered...by you.

24:23.807 --> 24:26.775
- That's never gonna happen.
- What do you think, Harvey?

24:26.777 --> 24:29.110
Do you think that's
"never gonna happen"?

24:29.112 --> 24:31.112
Like I said,
whatever you throw at us,

24:31.114 --> 24:32.847
we'll throw it
right the hell back.

24:32.849 --> 24:34.115
With what manpower?

24:34.117 --> 24:35.750
You wanna pick a fight

24:35.752 --> 24:37.152
with a little
regional law firm

24:37.154 --> 24:38.987
to flex your muscles,
go ahead.

24:38.989 --> 24:41.856
But we're five times
your size.

24:41.858 --> 24:44.993
This is a fight <i> you</i> started.

24:44.995 --> 24:47.829
And this is a fight
that you cannot win.

24:47.831 --> 24:50.131
So you give me back
my clients,

24:50.133 --> 24:52.767
or your legacy
at Pearson Specter Litt

24:52.769 --> 24:54.669
is going to be
that you were the one

24:54.671 --> 24:56.805
that put them in the ground.

24:56.807 --> 25:00.141
<i>[dark music]</i>

25:02.748 --> 25:04.681
Let me get this straight.

25:04.683 --> 25:06.617
I got an offer for more money

25:06.619 --> 25:08.151
than I'll see my whole life,

25:08.153 --> 25:09.786
and you want me
to turn it down

25:09.788 --> 25:11.822
based on a feeling that
whatever happened to Chris

25:11.824 --> 25:13.357
happened to other people?
- It's not a feeling.

25:13.359 --> 25:15.158
It's an instinct
that comes from

25:15.160 --> 25:16.760
working on hundreds
of cases like this.

25:16.762 --> 25:18.695
And if you take this deal,

25:18.697 --> 25:20.764
you're never gonna get
the answers you want.

25:20.766 --> 25:24.167
You'll never know
what happened to your son.

25:24.169 --> 25:26.169
And I have another son

25:26.171 --> 25:27.638
and two daughters,

25:27.640 --> 25:29.806
and this changes
their lives.

25:29.808 --> 25:31.908
- Mr. Reyes--
- Are you telling me

25:31.910 --> 25:34.244
that you can prove
they had something to do

25:34.246 --> 25:35.646
with my son's death?

25:35.648 --> 25:37.681
Yes. I believe

25:37.683 --> 25:40.083
that Oliver can get enough to--
- No, not Oliver.

25:40.085 --> 25:42.886
You. Because you're the one
who took my case,

25:42.888 --> 25:44.821
and then you backed out.
- I told you,

25:44.823 --> 25:47.691
there was a conflict.
- I don't know what that means.

25:47.693 --> 25:49.660
Then listen to me
right now.

25:49.662 --> 25:51.795
I know that you know my parents
died in a car accident.

25:51.797 --> 25:54.297
But what you don't know
is that after they did,

25:54.299 --> 25:56.733
a lawyer...came to my
grandmother

25:56.735 --> 25:58.702
and made her an offer.

25:58.704 --> 26:00.837
She took it,
instead of going to court.

26:00.839 --> 26:02.406
And I am telling you,

26:02.408 --> 26:05.208
she regretted that
for the rest of her life.

26:05.210 --> 26:10.380
Oscar, there's no price
that'll make the pain go away.

26:13.719 --> 26:15.152
Then what will?

26:15.154 --> 26:16.753
Doing everything you can

26:16.755 --> 26:19.389
to make sure no one else
ever has to feel it too.

26:19.391 --> 26:22.426
<i>[somber music]</i>

26:22.428 --> 26:25.262
At least, that's the closest
I've ever gotten.

26:25.264 --> 26:27.864
And you think
turning this down will do that.

26:27.866 --> 26:30.233
I think Chris is gone and
we can't ever bring him back.

26:30.235 --> 26:31.468
Which means this is about

26:31.470 --> 26:33.403
more than just money
or justice.

26:33.405 --> 26:36.773
It's about stopping other
people like him from dying.

26:36.775 --> 26:40.277
And I think it can be done,
but...

26:40.279 --> 26:42.446
even if it can't...

26:42.448 --> 26:43.914
we gotta try.

26:43.916 --> 26:46.883
<i>[somber music]</i>

26:46.885 --> 26:51.855
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:51.857 --> 26:53.890
Tell them no.

26:53.892 --> 27:00.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:02.968 --> 27:05.969
[phone rings]

27:05.971 --> 27:07.838
- Harvey, how'd it go?
<i>- Listen to me.</i>

27:07.840 --> 27:09.773
<i>I didn't think it mattered</i>
<i>before,</i>

27:09.775 --> 27:11.508
but they've got someone
feeding them inside information.

27:11.510 --> 27:13.210
I need to know who it is.

27:13.212 --> 27:15.312
I'm already working
on it, Harvey.

27:15.314 --> 27:17.013
<i>Good. 'Cause this is your</i>
<i>chance to prove to everybody</i>

27:17.015 --> 27:20.851
I made the right decision
giving you that promotion.

27:20.853 --> 27:22.819
Robert.

27:22.821 --> 27:24.888
We need to talk.
- From what I hear,

27:24.890 --> 27:26.757
you need to spend
less time talking

27:26.759 --> 27:28.458
and more time looking over
your firm.

27:28.460 --> 27:32.796
And you said if I needed
help doing that to let you know.

27:32.798 --> 27:33.797
All right.
Let's have it.

27:33.799 --> 27:35.432
What do you need?

27:35.434 --> 27:38.235
It's nothing you haven't
proposed to Jessica before.

27:38.237 --> 27:40.270
You gotta be kidding me.
You want to merge?

27:40.272 --> 27:41.471
I'm not talking about
a real merger.

27:41.473 --> 27:43.507
I'm talking about
putting out word

27:43.509 --> 27:45.342
that two of the best firms
in the city

27:45.344 --> 27:48.512
are now one of the biggest
firms in the city.

27:48.514 --> 27:50.547
You don't have the manpower
to fight him, do you?

27:50.549 --> 27:52.516
Bratton's making this
an arms race, Robert.

27:52.518 --> 27:54.518
If I don't have the numbers
to fight a war,

27:54.520 --> 27:56.419
I have to at least
make it look like I do.

27:56.421 --> 27:59.256
- I can't do it, Harvey.
- Robert, it's a bluff.

27:59.258 --> 28:01.224
A bluff with nothing
but downside for me.

28:01.226 --> 28:02.492
That's not true.
When this is over,

28:02.494 --> 28:04.361
you can have your pick
of the clients

28:04.363 --> 28:05.962
that came over from Bratton.
- When this is over,

28:05.964 --> 28:07.964
I'm gonna look like
I backed away from a merger,

28:07.966 --> 28:09.933
that I can't be trusted,
not to mention

28:09.935 --> 28:11.902
that I look like I'm so weak

28:11.904 --> 28:14.237
that I needed to merge with
a struggling firm like yours

28:14.239 --> 28:15.539
to begin with.
- Is that what you think

28:15.541 --> 28:18.842
we are--struggling?
- Harvey...

28:18.844 --> 28:21.077
you need me to answer
that...

28:21.079 --> 28:24.848
then you've got an even bigger
problem than Tommy Bratton.

28:24.850 --> 28:27.584
<i>[lightly edgy music]</i>

28:27.586 --> 28:34.891
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:36.528 --> 28:38.395
Harvey, please tell me Zane
went for the merger idea.

28:38.397 --> 28:39.963
- He didn't.
- Damn it! We're gonna drown

28:39.965 --> 28:41.531
without any help.
- Then we'll get help.

28:41.533 --> 28:43.333
What do you think
we've been working on?

28:43.335 --> 28:45.068
I thought you were trying
to find the leak.

28:45.070 --> 28:46.536
- We were, but we can't.
- And since Zane might say no,

28:46.538 --> 28:48.905
I put out some feelers
with headhunters

28:48.907 --> 28:50.874
to see about getting some
first-years and paralegals.

28:50.876 --> 28:52.509
The problem is, we need
a minimum of 2 dozen each

28:52.511 --> 28:54.411
to handle the workload,
but it's gonna run us

28:54.413 --> 28:56.012
over 3 million a year.
- Then we'll get a bridge loan

28:56.014 --> 28:58.014
from your guy at Fidelity.
- We already used

28:58.016 --> 29:01.084
that line of credit last year
when we expanded the 42nd floor.

29:01.086 --> 29:02.319
- Shit.
- Harvey, what the hell

29:02.321 --> 29:04.054
are we gonna do?

29:04.056 --> 29:06.923
I don't see a way out of this.
- I have a way out.

29:06.925 --> 29:08.491
Give them what they want.

29:08.493 --> 29:09.960
I'm not giving up
your clients, Alex.

29:09.962 --> 29:11.528
I do that, I might as well
let you go.

29:11.530 --> 29:13.330
Then let me go,
because I'm not gonna

29:13.332 --> 29:15.031
be responsible
for driving you in the ground.

29:15.033 --> 29:17.567
- No, I'm not gonna do that.
- Why the hell not?

29:17.569 --> 29:19.002
Because you're one of us now.

29:19.004 --> 29:20.570
And I agree.

29:20.572 --> 29:22.572
Well, what are we
gonna do?

29:22.574 --> 29:24.341
You're gonna go back
to finding out

29:24.343 --> 29:26.443
who's feeding them
inside information,

29:26.445 --> 29:27.911
and you two
are gonna figure out

29:27.913 --> 29:29.579
who they're coming after
first.

29:29.581 --> 29:32.916
And I'm gonna figure out how to
beat this son of a bitch.

29:32.918 --> 29:35.151
<i>[dramatic musical buildup]</i>

29:35.153 --> 29:38.121
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:40.559 --> 29:42.158
Mike, hey.
How'd it go?

29:42.160 --> 29:44.394
- He turned the offer down.
- Thank God.

29:44.396 --> 29:46.363
I thought you'd be
disappointed.

29:46.365 --> 29:48.131
That was before
I found this...

29:48.133 --> 29:51.434
and this...

29:51.436 --> 29:53.470
and this.

29:53.472 --> 29:55.939
- Holy shit.
- You were right.

29:55.941 --> 29:57.674
As soon as I started
looking in the right places,

29:57.676 --> 29:59.609
all the apples started
falling from the tree.

29:59.611 --> 30:01.378
There's gotta be
at least 20 complaints

30:01.380 --> 30:03.647
of prisoners being denied
their release date.

30:03.649 --> 30:05.181
And every one of them
involves injuries

30:05.183 --> 30:07.117
and some kind of vague
disciplinary action.

30:07.119 --> 30:09.085
Jesus. They're not just
cheaping out on medical care.

30:09.087 --> 30:11.488
They're manufacturing revenue.

30:11.490 --> 30:14.090
[laughs]
Oliver, this...

30:14.092 --> 30:15.992
This is unbelievable.
You got a class now.

30:15.994 --> 30:17.560
There's only one problem.

30:17.562 --> 30:20.196
I don't have the resources
to handle this alone.

30:20.198 --> 30:22.098
Oliver, we've been
over this.

30:22.100 --> 30:24.100
I signed an agreement
that said I wouldn't touch it.

30:24.102 --> 30:26.369
I can't cross that line.
- Jesus Christ, Mike.

30:26.371 --> 30:28.104
You're telling me you care
more about some

30:28.106 --> 30:29.606
piece of paper you signed
than about these men's lives?

30:29.608 --> 30:31.474
No, I don't,
but I signed it.

30:31.476 --> 30:33.376
Which means if I get involved
and they find out,

30:33.378 --> 30:35.445
the case gets tossed,
and Oscar gets nothing.

30:35.447 --> 30:37.380
You lived a lie for years.
You're telling me

30:37.382 --> 30:40.050
you can't keep a secret
about working one Goddamn case?

30:40.052 --> 30:41.618
- I gave Harvey my word.
- So what the hell

30:41.620 --> 30:43.687
am I supposed to do?
- You're supposed to

30:43.689 --> 30:46.089
convince Nathan to give you
the resources to pursue this.

30:46.091 --> 30:47.958
And when I can't and I have to
go back and tell Oscar

30:47.960 --> 30:49.993
that we can't
move forward with this...

30:49.995 --> 30:51.194
that's gonna be on you.

30:51.196 --> 30:58.201
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:58.203 --> 31:00.236
I know how to
take down Bratton.

31:00.238 --> 31:01.972
Alex,
we've been over this.

31:01.974 --> 31:03.707
I am not giving up you
or your clients.

31:03.709 --> 31:06.476
I'm not talking about that.
I got something on him.

31:06.478 --> 31:08.178
Why is this the first
I'm hearing about this?

31:08.180 --> 31:10.013
You know why.

31:10.015 --> 31:11.648
Because whatever it is,

31:11.650 --> 31:13.750
he's got the same
damn thing on you.

31:13.752 --> 31:16.019
Son of a bitch.

31:16.021 --> 31:17.554
You should have told me
this before.

31:17.556 --> 31:19.122
I couldn't.
You never would've hired me.

31:19.124 --> 31:20.690
I meant when they started
coming after us.

31:20.692 --> 31:22.058
I was hoping I wouldn't
have to use it.

31:22.060 --> 31:23.660
Well, now I do.
What is it?

31:23.662 --> 31:25.662
- I can't tell you.
- Are you kidding me?

31:25.664 --> 31:27.697
As long as I don't tell you,
you're not party to it.

31:27.699 --> 31:29.265
I'm not gonna expose you
like that.

31:29.267 --> 31:31.067
I'm gonna take care
of this myself.

31:31.069 --> 31:32.469
If you're gonna do that,

31:32.471 --> 31:34.204
then why are you even
coming to me?

31:34.206 --> 31:36.172
Because you took me in.
I'm a part of this firm now,

31:36.174 --> 31:38.041
and if I do this, I'm not
sure what's gonna come of it.

31:38.043 --> 31:40.210
That's not good enough.
You go over there and do this,

31:40.212 --> 31:42.212
you sure as hell
better make it work.

31:42.214 --> 31:45.482
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

31:45.484 --> 31:49.652
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:51.458 --> 31:53.458
All right, good.
We'll wrap this up tomorrow.

31:53.460 --> 31:54.793
Thanks.

32:00.834 --> 32:03.335
I was wondering when
you'd come crawling back.

32:03.337 --> 32:04.636
I'm back,
but I'm not crawling.

32:04.638 --> 32:06.238
I'm here to tell you

32:06.240 --> 32:07.739
you're backing the hell off
my firm.

32:07.741 --> 32:10.542
I know what you're here to do,
but let me ask you this.

32:10.544 --> 32:13.345
Does your firm know what it is
that you did?

32:13.347 --> 32:14.779
No. But if you don't
let this shit go,

32:14.781 --> 32:17.616
they're not gonna be
the only ones I tell.

32:17.618 --> 32:20.552
And not just what I did.
What you did.

32:22.689 --> 32:24.522
I let this shit go,

32:24.524 --> 32:27.325
and it comes back
and hits you in the ass.

32:29.463 --> 32:30.729
You're gonna sign something

32:30.731 --> 32:33.832
saying I had
nothing to do with this.

32:33.834 --> 32:35.767
I already did.

32:35.769 --> 32:39.738
Just like I also prepared
something for you to sign

32:39.740 --> 32:42.340
saying you won't so much
as look at any of our clients

32:42.342 --> 32:44.476
for the next ten years.

32:44.478 --> 32:47.479
<i>[lightly edgy music]</i>

32:47.481 --> 32:49.714
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:49.716 --> 32:52.050
- You're willing to do this.
- Like I said.

32:52.052 --> 32:54.386
I already did it.

32:55.455 --> 32:56.454
[paper slaps down]

32:56.456 --> 32:57.856
[pen scratching]

32:59.660 --> 33:02.327
It's on you now.

33:02.329 --> 33:05.463
Yes. It is.

33:05.465 --> 33:11.569
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:13.674 --> 33:16.074
Is it done?

33:16.076 --> 33:17.542
What do you think?

33:17.544 --> 33:19.411
I think you probably
went in there

33:19.413 --> 33:21.713
and said something like, "You're
gonna drop these lawsuits

33:21.715 --> 33:23.515
"and you're gonna forget
about coming after

33:23.517 --> 33:25.350
any of our clients."

33:25.352 --> 33:27.919
And he said, "Our clients?
Don't you mean my clients?"

33:27.921 --> 33:31.890
And I said, "No,
motherfu--er, I don't.

33:31.892 --> 33:33.925
"Because I'm at
Pearson Specter now,

33:33.927 --> 33:37.362
and he's not getting
my clients."

33:38.632 --> 33:40.598
You're twice the man
he is, Alex.

33:40.600 --> 33:42.567
- What do you mean?
- I mean if the ship

33:42.569 --> 33:44.703
were sinking, Tommy Bratton
would throw his best friend

33:44.705 --> 33:47.405
overboard
to get himself to shore.

33:47.407 --> 33:49.774
You, on the other hand,
would offer him a life raft.

33:49.776 --> 33:51.710
Thanks, Harvey.

33:51.712 --> 33:54.979
No, Alex.
Thank you.

34:00.387 --> 34:01.820
Hey...

34:01.822 --> 34:03.722
what are we gonna tell
Louis and Donna

34:03.724 --> 34:05.490
about how this all went away?

34:05.492 --> 34:07.425
We're gonna tell them
we did whatever it took.

34:07.427 --> 34:10.462
And for the record,
Louis is right.

34:10.464 --> 34:12.530
You are one of us now.

34:16.837 --> 34:18.969
Don't tell Louis
I said he was right.

34:18.972 --> 34:20.972
Don't worry about it.
I only listen to

34:20.974 --> 34:23.742
every third thing you say
anyway.

34:23.744 --> 34:26.678
<i>[quiet music]</i>

34:26.679 --> 34:28.580
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:28.581 --> 34:29.947
[knock on glass]
- Hey.

34:29.949 --> 34:32.751
- Hey.
- I just realized I never

34:32.753 --> 34:35.553
asked how the meeting
at the Plaza went.

34:35.554 --> 34:37.522
Um...

34:37.524 --> 34:39.924
I canceled it.

34:39.926 --> 34:42.627
- I don't understand.
- I got there late,

34:42.629 --> 34:44.795
and the woman started
showing me options anyway.

34:44.797 --> 34:46.531
But I realized...

34:46.533 --> 34:48.533
I was spending more time
thinking about

34:48.534 --> 34:50.969
who was feeding Bratton Gould
inside information

34:50.971 --> 34:53.004
than I was about

34:53.005 --> 34:55.507
what color our napkins
were going to be.

34:55.509 --> 34:58.443
So you don't wanna have it
at the Plaza anymore?

34:58.445 --> 35:01.179
No, that's not it.
Mike, what's wrong with us?

35:01.181 --> 35:03.681
We can't even find the time
to keep one appointment.

35:03.683 --> 35:05.850
Rachel, come on, our schedules
are crazy right now.

35:05.852 --> 35:08.620
And that's exactly what I told
my dad when he brought it up.

35:08.622 --> 35:10.555
Brought what up?

35:10.557 --> 35:13.558
He said that if we can't make
time for each other right now,

35:13.560 --> 35:16.027
how are we gonna
make time for our marriage?

35:16.029 --> 35:17.529
Hey.

35:20.901 --> 35:25.603
You are the most
important thing in my life.

35:25.605 --> 35:27.605
If you wanna
drop everything right now

35:27.607 --> 35:30.008
and plan the wedding
and the honeymoon

35:30.010 --> 35:31.876
and start picking out
baby names,

35:31.878 --> 35:33.511
then that's what
we'll do.

35:33.513 --> 35:34.946
That's the thing.

35:34.948 --> 35:36.948
I don't wanna drop
everything right now.

35:36.950 --> 35:38.950
I wanna get married...

35:38.952 --> 35:42.520
but I also really care
about what I do.

35:42.522 --> 35:44.456
Maybe your father's right.

35:44.458 --> 35:45.957
- Mike--
- No, I mean that he's right

35:45.959 --> 35:47.959
about how hard it is for us
to throw ourselves

35:47.961 --> 35:50.728
into our wedding right now,
but...

35:50.730 --> 35:52.730
he's wrong if he thinks
we never will.

35:52.732 --> 35:54.699
- What does that mean?
- That means

35:54.701 --> 35:56.568
that I care about
what I do too.

35:56.570 --> 35:58.670
And right now I gotta
go take care of something

35:58.672 --> 36:01.039
that I should have
taken care of before, but...

36:01.041 --> 36:03.041
when we get home,

36:03.043 --> 36:04.676
we're gonna crack open
a bottle of wine,

36:04.678 --> 36:06.511
and we're gonna talk
all night

36:06.513 --> 36:08.913
about the kind of wedding
we wanna have.

36:08.915 --> 36:11.082
And then we are gonna
pick a date.

36:11.084 --> 36:13.618
Really?

36:13.620 --> 36:15.019
Really.

36:15.021 --> 36:18.022
<i>[emotional instrumentals]</i>

36:18.024 --> 36:25.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:30.637 --> 36:32.036
Harvey, I know you're
coming in here to--

36:32.038 --> 36:33.872
Donna, relax.
I came over here to tell you

36:33.874 --> 36:35.640
that it's over.

36:35.642 --> 36:37.642
Why don't you go home
and get some rest?

36:37.644 --> 36:41.613
I know you've been working
around the clock on this thing.

36:41.615 --> 36:43.615
I'm sorry, Harvey.

36:43.617 --> 36:46.017
- What do you mean?
- You promoted me.

36:46.019 --> 36:47.919
You had faith in me,

36:47.921 --> 36:49.921
and I never found out
who it was--I let you down.

36:49.923 --> 36:51.756
Donna, you haven't
let me down in 12 years,

36:51.758 --> 36:54.025
and you didn't start now.

36:54.027 --> 36:57.295
Besides, whoever it was...

36:57.297 --> 36:59.030
doesn't matter anymore.

36:59.032 --> 37:02.000
<i>[mellow pop music]</i>

37:02.002 --> 37:09.073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:12.746 --> 37:13.945
[line ringing]

37:13.947 --> 37:16.548
[phone rings]

37:16.550 --> 37:18.049
[ringing]

37:18.051 --> 37:19.918
Hello?

37:19.920 --> 37:21.619
<i>It was you, wasn't it?</i>

37:21.621 --> 37:22.787
What was me?

37:22.789 --> 37:24.122
Don't bullshit me, Jessica.

37:24.124 --> 37:25.790
You called Tommy Bratton

37:25.792 --> 37:27.158
and gave him the roadmap
to me and Louis,

37:27.160 --> 37:28.793
and I wanna know why.

37:28.795 --> 37:30.662
<i>If you figured</i> that <i> out,</i>

37:30.664 --> 37:32.797
<i>then you already know why.</i>
- I want an answer.

37:32.799 --> 37:35.633
You came to me saying
that your house was divided.

37:35.635 --> 37:37.669
And whether you like
hearing it or not, Harvey,

37:37.671 --> 37:41.573
<i>nothing unites a divided house</i>
<i>like an attack from the outside.</i>

37:41.575 --> 37:43.107
That doesn't mean you pick up
the phone and call him.

37:43.109 --> 37:45.810
I didn't call him.
He called me.

37:45.812 --> 37:47.845
He was coming anyway, Harvey.

37:47.847 --> 37:49.948
All I did was mention that...

37:49.950 --> 37:51.015
I didn't like the way
I was treated

37:51.017 --> 37:52.684
on my way out the door,

37:52.686 --> 37:54.986
<i>and if he wanted</i>
<i>to get to you,</i>

37:54.988 --> 37:56.688
<i>he should play you</i>
<i>against Louis.</i>

37:56.690 --> 37:58.056
Jessica, I called you
for advice,

37:58.058 --> 37:59.924
not so that you'd
go behind the scenes

37:59.926 --> 38:01.726
and manipulate things.
<i>- Harvey.</i>

38:01.728 --> 38:03.027
- You said I was ready.
-<i> You are.</i>

38:03.029 --> 38:04.796
<i>And now they know you are,</i>

38:04.798 --> 38:08.099
and they're behind you
for the next time.

38:10.804 --> 38:13.972
- I guess I should thank you.
<i>- You're welcome, Harvey.</i>

38:13.974 --> 38:16.608
But you pull something
like this again...

38:16.610 --> 38:18.977
I won't have to.

38:20.847 --> 38:22.680
Good night, Jessica.

38:22.682 --> 38:24.215
Good night, Harvey.

38:24.217 --> 38:27.218
<i>[mellow pop song]</i>

38:27.220 --> 38:34.192
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:34.194 --> 38:37.762
[phone rings]

38:37.764 --> 38:40.732
- Well, look who it is.
<i>- What are you doing?</i>

38:40.734 --> 38:44.135
<i>Just getting ready</i>
<i>for trial tomorrow.</i>

38:44.137 --> 38:46.404
It never stops, does it?

38:46.406 --> 38:49.140
<i>- What's that?</i>
- The work of being a lawyer.

38:49.142 --> 38:52.744
Doesn't mean you
can't make time for...

38:52.746 --> 38:55.013
The more important things.
<i>- Speaking of the more</i>

38:55.015 --> 38:57.181
important things--I set
a meeting with the planner

38:57.183 --> 38:59.050
at the Plaza.

38:59.052 --> 39:01.152
It's gonna be wonderful.

39:01.154 --> 39:02.887
Thank you.

39:02.889 --> 39:05.023
Aw, you don't have to
thank me, Rachel.

39:05.025 --> 39:07.959
All I want is for your wedding
to be exactly what you want.

39:07.961 --> 39:09.894
<i>And what I want</i>
<i>is gonna take some time,</i>

39:09.896 --> 39:10.928
<i>because, Dad, you were right.</i>

39:10.930 --> 39:14.065
I want to...enjoy it

39:14.067 --> 39:16.868
and make time for it.

39:16.870 --> 39:19.170
So Mike and I
are gonna set a date,

39:19.172 --> 39:21.773
but it's not gonna be
for a while.

39:21.775 --> 39:23.908
Well, it doesn't matter
when it is.

39:23.910 --> 39:25.977
As long as you're happy.

39:25.979 --> 39:29.847
<i>Good. Because there's</i>
<i>something else I wanted to say.</i>

39:31.117 --> 39:33.151
I heard this idea
of a fake merger

39:33.153 --> 39:35.920
between us was floated.
<i>- Let me guess.</i>

39:35.922 --> 39:39.090
You think I should have
helped Harvey out.

39:39.092 --> 39:41.793
<i>No. What I was gonna say</i>
<i>was even though it was fake,</i>

39:41.795 --> 39:45.296
I got kind of excited about the
thought of working with my dad.

39:45.298 --> 39:50.201
<i>[soft music]</i>

39:50.203 --> 39:52.737
I never thought
I'd ever hear you say that.

39:52.739 --> 39:55.039
<i>Well, Katrina told me</i>
<i>that you said something once</i>

39:55.041 --> 39:57.475
that I was afraid
I'd never hear, and...

39:57.477 --> 39:59.210
[sighs]

39:59.212 --> 40:01.212
It meant everything to me.

40:01.214 --> 40:02.980
And what's that?

40:02.982 --> 40:05.216
That you think
I'm a great lawyer.

40:05.218 --> 40:07.819
And that you're proud of me.

40:10.190 --> 40:12.256
Rachel...

40:12.258 --> 40:16.227
I may not say it often enough.

40:16.229 --> 40:19.063
But I think it all the time.

40:20.867 --> 40:24.102
I love you, Dad.

40:25.805 --> 40:27.939
I love you too, baby.

40:27.941 --> 40:30.942
<i>[emotional music]</i>

40:30.944 --> 40:37.915
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:37.917 --> 40:39.884
[phone rings]

40:39.886 --> 40:41.953
[ringing]

40:41.955 --> 40:43.821
- Hello.
<i>- Oliver, it's me.</i>

40:43.823 --> 40:45.957
<i>Sorry, Mike,</i>
<i>I can't talk right now.</i>

40:45.959 --> 40:48.526
I'm kinda busy being overwhelmed
by a case I can't handle.

40:48.528 --> 40:50.795
I take it you couldn't
convince Nathan

40:50.797 --> 40:53.164
to get you more people?
<i>- No. I couldn't.</i>

40:53.166 --> 40:56.968
Well, in that case...

40:56.970 --> 40:58.936
I'm in.

40:58.938 --> 41:01.105
What about your promise
to Harvey?

41:02.909 --> 41:04.876
You let me worry
about Harvey.

41:04.878 --> 41:07.879
<i>[soulful music]</i>

41:07.881 --> 41:10.948
<i>♪ ♪</i>

